stice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20said%20in%20his%20address%20at%20the%20Oxford%20Union%20Society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20the%20famous%20University%20of%20Oxford%20institution%20on%20Tuesday%20on%20the%20topic%20of%20the%20humanising%20role%20adjudicators%20can%20play%20in%20society%2C%20the%20senior-most%20judge%20of%20India's%20top%20court%20highlighted%20the%20role%20of%20technology%20in%20injecting%20greater%20transparency%20into%20the%20judicial%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcknowledging%20some%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bunfair%26quot%3B%20criticism%20aimed%20at%20judges%20on%20social%20media%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20asserted%20that%20the%20overall%20impact%20of%20technology%20is%20to%20help%20the%20judiciary%20reach%20out%20to%20a%20wider%20section%20of%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BElections%20lie%20at%20the%20core%20of%20constitutional%20democracy%20...%20judges%20are%20not%20elected%20in%20India%20and%20for%20a%20reason%3B%20judges%20reflect%20a%20sense%20of%20continuity%20of%20conditions%2C%20a%20continuity%20of%20constitutional%20values%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20response%20to%20a%20question%20referencing%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20the%20results%20of%20which%20were%20declared%20earlier%20in%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20judiciary%20has%20a%20vital%20role%20to%20play%20in%20a%20democracy%2C%20which%20is%20that%20we%20reflect%20a%20sense%20of%20tradition%20and%20we%20also%20reflect%20a%20sense%20of%20what%20the%20future%20of%20a%20good%20society%20should%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20Chief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20political%20and%20societal%20pressures%20he%20may%20have%20faced%20while%20handing%20down%20judgments%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20stated%20that%20he%20has%20never%20faced%20a%20%26quot%3Bsense%20of%20political%20pressure%20from%20the%20powers%20that%20be%26quot%3B%20in%20his%2024%20years%20as%20a%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20live%20lives%20which%20are%20relatively%20isolated%20from%20the%20political%20arm%20of%20the%20government%20...%20but%20obviously%20judges%20have%20to%20be%20conversant%20with%20the%20impact%20of%20their%20decisions%20on%20the%20polity%20at%20large.%20That's%20not%20political%20pressure%20but%20an%20understanding%20by%20the%20court%20of%20the%20likely%20impact%20of%20a%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%2C%20who%20took%20questions%20from%20the%20student%20audience%20members%2C%20was%20asked%20about%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20judgment%20that%20ruled%20against%20legalising%20same-sex%20marriage%20in%20India%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20here%20to%20defend%20the%20judgment%20because%2C%20as%20a%20judge%2C%20I%20believe%20once%20a%20judgment%20is%20delivered%2C%20it%20becomes%20the%20property%20of%20not%20just%20the%20nation%20but%20global%20humanity.%20The%20Special%20Marriage%20Act%20was%20a%20law%20enacted%20by%20Parliament%20...%20which%20contemplates%20a%20marriage%20in%20a%20heterosexual%20relationship%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20going%20on%20to%20share%20that%20he%20was%20in%20the%20minority%20in%20that%20case%20in%20a%20certain%20specific%20aspect%20as%20he%20was%20in%20favour%20of%20recognising%20civil%20unions%20for%20same-sex%20couples%20%26quot%3Buntil%20such%20time%20as%20Parliament%20stepped%20in%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThree%20of%20my%20colleagues%20didn't%20agree%20with%20us%20because%20they%20felt%20even%20the%20recognition%20of%20same-sex%20unions%20was%20beyond%20the%20purview%20of%20the%20court%20...%20What%20happens%20in%20courts%20in%20modern%20democracies%20is%20not%20really%20to%20be%20looked%20at%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20substantive%20outcomes%20of%20the%20case.%20The%20court%20is%20involved%20in%20a%20continuous%20process%20of%20dialogue%2C%20not%20only%20with%20the%20litigating%20parties%20but%20a%20dialogue%20with%20civil%20society%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20main%20motivation%20behind%20his%20decision%20to%20livestream%20important%20constitutional%20cases%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20take%20the%20process%20of%20justice%20and%20the%20administration%20of%20law%20to%20the%20homes%20and%20the%20hearts%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20independent%2C%20student-led%20society%20with%20a%20membership%20primarily%20drawn%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Oxford%2C%20the%20Oxford%20Union%20Society%2C%20commonly%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20Oxford%20Union%2C%20dates%20back%20to%201823%20as%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20leading%20debating%20societies%20created%20to%20uphold%20the%20principles%20of%20free%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20keynote%20address%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20spoke%20at%20length%20about%20the%20judiciary%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20justice%20that%20brings%20order%20and%20certainty%20and%20combats%20the%20dehumanising%20effects%20in%20society%20through%20a%20humanising%20approach%20towards%20adjudication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTechnological%20intervention%20has%20humanised%20the%20process%20for%20the%20parties%20and%20the%20administrative%20staff%20of%20our%20courts.%20It%20is%20my%20duty%2C%20however%2C%20to%20place%20a%20small%20caveat%3A%20I'm%20not%20a%20proponent%20of%20the%20complete%20automation%20of%20procedures.%20Since%20I%20believe%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20human%20mind%20will%20remove%20the%20human%20element%20from%20the%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20important%20that%20we%20understand%20and%20value%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20technological%20usage%20to%20ensure%20a%20humanised%20mechanism%20of%20justice.%20Artificial%20Intelligence%20is%20replete%20with%20unique%20possibilities%20for%20the%20future.%20We%20must%20also%20ensure%20that%20we%20impose%20guardrails%20to%20control%20Artificial%20Intelligence%20itself%20and%20not%20shift%20the%20process%20of%20communication%20from%20a%20judge%20to%20a%20robot%2C%26quot%3B%20Chief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717564200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2F374d7jlg_dy-chandrachud-_625x300_20_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnever-faced-political-pressure-chief-justice-chandrachud-at-oxford-union-5821595%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20elections%20lie%20at%20the%20core%20of%20India's%20constitutional%20democracy%2C%20judges%20reflect%20a%20sense%20of%20continuity%20of%20constitutional%20values%20that%20protect%20the%20system%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20said%20in%20his%20address%20at%20the%20Oxford%20Union%20Society.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnever-faced-political-pressure-chief-justice-chandrachud-at-oxford-union-5821595%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnever-faced-political-pressure-chief-justice-chandrachud-at-oxford-union-5821595%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnever-faced-political-pressure-chief-justice-chandrachud-at-oxford-union-5821595%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22OnePlus%20announces%20community%20sale%20offers%20on%20OP%2012%2C%20Open%2C%20Nord%20CE4%2C%20and%20more%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717564059000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-06%2F05%2Fthumb%2Ffeaturecrop%2F400X400%2F1717563810-5332.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2