20come%20too%20late%20to%20be%20meaningful%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20lifespans%20increasing%2C%20and%20both%20parents%20and%20children%20living%20longer%2C%C2%A0%20inheritances%20are%20coming%20later%20and%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20any%20income%20group%20you%20look%20at%2C%20the%20age%20of%20'inheritance%20receipt'%20peaks%20at%20around%2060.%20That's%20a%20natural%20result%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20most%20common%20life%20span%20is%2080%20and%20the%20most%20common%20age%20gap%20between%20parents%20and%20children%20is%2020%2C%26quot%3B%20Perkins%20writes%2C%20citing%20a%20report%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20people%2C%2060%20isn't%20when%20that%20money%20would%20make%20the%20most%20impact.%20The%20average%20net%20worth%20in%20this%20age%20group%2C%20in%20households%20headed%20by%20someone%20aged%2055%20to%2064%2C%20is%20over%20%241%20million.%20People%20in%20this%20age%20group%20have%20already%20likely%20planned%20for%20retirement%20on%20their%20own%2C%20sent%20children%20to%20college%2C%20and%20even%20paid%20off%20a%20mortgage.%20For%20that%20reason%2C%20Perkins%20writes%20that%20the%20money%20could%20be%20better%20used%20earlier%20in%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInheritances%20have%20largely%2C%20and%20perhaps%20unintentionally%2C%20become%20retirement%20funds%20for%20middle-class%20retirees%20above%20all%20else.%20%26quot%3BInheritances%20used%20to%20go%20more%20toward%20mid-career%2C%20mid-life%20expenses%20like%20kids%2C%20and%20now%20they're%20likely%20going%20more%20toward%20concerns%20of%20people%20in%20their%2050s%2C%20which%20is%20saving%20for%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20Lincoln%20Plews%2C%20a%20research%20analyst%20at%20United%20Income%20from%20Capital%20One%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGet%20Exclusive%20Savings%20with%20Raisin%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Open%20one%20of%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-high-yield-savings-accounts-rates-right-now%5C%22%3E%20best%20savings%20accounts%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20no-fee%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fraisin-review%5C%22%3E%20Raisin%3C%2Fa%3E%20account%20in%20minutes%20and%20spread%20your%20savings%20across%20an%20exclusive%20network%20of%20over%2030%20FDIC-insured%20banks%20and%20NCUA-insured%20credit%20unions.%20Earn%20top%20savings%20rates%20and%20manage%20it%20all%20with%20a%20single%20secure%20login.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3EGiving%20money%20sooner%20than%20later%20can%20benefit%20children%20both%20short-%20and%20long-term%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPerkins%20cites%20the%20example%20of%20one%20woman%20who%20struggled%20for%20years%20financially%20while%20raising%20her%20own%20children%2C%20only%20to%20receive%20an%20inheritance%20at%2049%20once%20her%20mother%20died.%20In%20an%20interview%20with%20one%20of%20Perkins'%20colleagues%2C%20this%20woman%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20have%20been%20more%20valuable%20a%20lot%20earlier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20in%20their%2050s%20and%2060s%20have%20had%20years%20to%20start%20saving%2C%20investing%2C%20and%20probably%20have%20established%20a%20life%20for%20themselves.%20Meanwhile%2C%20younger%20generations%2C%20including%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Z%2C%20face%20large%20amounts%20of%20student%20debt%2C%20a%20tough%20job%20market%2C%20and%20high%20housing%20prices.%20They're%20at%20a%20stage%20in%20their%20lives%20where%20an%20inheritance%20could%20not%20only%20allow%20them%20to%20build%20a%20life%2C%20but%20also%20free%20up%20money%20to%20start%20saving%20for%20their%20own%20retirement%20funds%2C%20or%20start%20a%20family%20of%20their%20own.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolling%20his%20Twitter%20followers%2C%20Perkins%20writes%20that%20over%20half%20of%20the%203%2C500%20voters%20chose%20the%20ages%2026%20to%2035%20as%20the%20best%20age%20to%20receive%20an%20inheritance.%20That's%20the%20opposite%20of%20when%20people%20actually%20receive%20them%20in%20their%2060s.%20By%20that%20point%2C%20the%20money%20is%20too%20late%20to%20use%20when%20it's%20needed%2C%20and%20doesn't%20have%20as%20much%20time%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%3Ecompound%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20grow%C2%A0in%20the%20recipient's%20lifetime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20pattern%20of%20later-in-life%20inheritances%20is%20something%20that%20Perkins%20hopes%20his%20%26quot%3BDie%20with%20Zero%26quot%3B%20strategy%20reverses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20kids%2C%20'Die%20With%20Zero'%20shows%20thoughtfulness%20by%20having%20put%20your%20kids%20first%2C%20which%20you%20do%20by%20thinking%20deliberately%20about%20how%20much%20to%20give%20them%20and%20then%20doing%20so%2C%20before%20you%20die%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20writes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20in%20May%202021.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-inheritances-dont-help-children-die-with-zero-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1717538341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f1f28c34dca6826ad5a4df4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-inheritances-dont-help-children-die-with-zero-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Inheritances%20miss%20children%20when%20they%20need%20them%20most%3B%20the%20average%20recipient%20is%20well%20past%20the%20age%20when%20they%20need%20the%20money.%20Give%20intermittently%20instead.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Liz%20Knueven)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-inheritances-dont-help-children-die-with-zero-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20b