lth%20Services%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20%26amp%3B%20Family%20Welfare%2C%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20some%20of%20the%20challenges%20in%20deceased%20organ%20donation%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHuge%20demand-supply%20gap.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPoor%20infrastructure%2C%20especially%20in%20government%20hospitals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELack%20of%20awareness%20of%20brain%20death%20among%20stakeholders.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPoor%20rate%20of%20brain%20death%20certification%20by%20hospitals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELack%20of%20awareness%20and%20negative%20attitude%20towards%20deceased%20organ%20donation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELack%20of%20organised%20systems%20for%20organ%20procurement%20from%20deceased%20donors.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMaintenance%20of%20standards%20in%20organ%20retrieval%2C%20tissue%20banking%2C%20and%20transplantation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHigh%20cost%20of%20transplantation%2C%20especially%20for%20uninsured%20and%20poor%20patients.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20DGHS%2C%20the%20National%20Organ%20and%20Tissue%20Transplant%20Organisation%20(NOTTO)%20takes%20responsibility%20for%20the%20following%20actions%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMaintaining%20the%20waiting%20list%20of%20terminally%20ill%20patients%20requiring%20transplants%20%E2%80%93%20with%20details%20of%20hospital%2C%20organ%20needed%2C%20blood%20group%20and%20age%20of%20patient%2C%20urgency%2C%20and%20seniority%20in%20the%20waiting%20list.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMatching%20recipients%20with%20donors.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENetworking%20with%20transplant%20centres%2C%20retrieval%20centres%20and%20tissue%20banks.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECoordination%20of%20all%20activities%20required%20for%20procurement%20of%20organs%20and%20tissues%2C%20including%20medico-legal%20aspects.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAssigning%20the%20organ%20retrieval%20team%20and%20making%20arrangements%20for%20transporting%20the%20organs%20to%20the%20allocated%20locations.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20796px)%20100vw%2C%20796px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22796%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Actress%20Revathi%20holding%20up%20her%20donor%20card.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930.jpg%20796w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930-500x333.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930-768x511.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FActress-Revathi-holding-up-a-donor-card-1717420930-150x100.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-351951%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EActress%20Revathi%20holding%20up%20her%20donor%20card.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECounselling%20the%20family%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20Dr%20Shroff%20set%20up%20a%20protocol%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98Ramachandra%20Protocol%E2%80%99%20while%20asking%20the%20family%E2%80%99s%20consent%20for%20organ%20donation.%20The%20doctors%20would%20start%20by%20asking%20for%20eye%20donation%20first%20since%20it%20was%20already%20popular%2C%20and%20then%20for%20the%20other%20organs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTalking%20about%20organ%20donation%20is%20not%20easy%20at%20a%20time%20of%20grief.%20We%20need%20to%20treat%20the%20grieving%20family%20sensitively%20and%20support%20them.%20We%20have%20to%20first%20convey%20to%20the%20family%20that%20their%20loved%20one%20is%20brain%20dead.%20We%20need%20to%20then%20explain%20what%20brain%20death%20is.%20We%20let%20the%20message%20sink%20in%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20five%20to%20six%20hours%2C%20before%20we%20switch%20off%20the%20ventilator%2C%20we%20ask%20the%20family%20whether%20they%20wish%20to%20donate%20the%20organs.%20We%20tell%20them%20that%20they%20can%20save%20many%20lives%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20brain%20deaths%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F131027%2Fblood-donation-record-rotary%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edue%20to%20road%20accidents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Doctors%20have%20two%20to%20three%20days%20after%20brain%20deaths%20to%20do%20a%20transplant%20surgery.%20Certifying%20a%20brain%20death%20is%20a%20complex%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%2C%20the%20counsellors%20start%20a%20conversation%20with%20the%20family.%20If%20the%20family%20is%20convinced%2C%20multiple%20organs%20are%20harvested%20and%20distributed%20for%20transplant%20as%20per%20the%20waiting%20list%20of%20recipients.%20There%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20team%20work%20involved%20which%20is%20done%20by%20coordinators%20trained%20by%20the%20MOHAN%20Foundation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAge%20is%20no%20bar%20for%20organ%20donation.%20Our%20oldest%20donor%20was%20an%2088-year-old%20trustee%20of%20the%20Gangaram%20Hospital.%20When%20he%20was%20declared%20brain%20dead%2C%20his%20kidneys%20and%20liver%20were%20transplanted.%20However%2C%20we%20are%20cautious%20about%20taking%20the%20heart%20and%20lungs%20of%20a%20donor%20who%20is%20above%2060%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Shroff.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201768px)%20100vw%2C%201768px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FWith-a-